{"to":["mark@dynatechindustries.com"],"subject":"Procurement Data & Supplier Info – Budget Forecast","body":"Hi Mark,

As requested, please find below a concise overview of the latest procurement data covering the last two quarters (FY-2025 Q1–Q2). Detailed documents are available in our shared "Budget Forecast" folder on SharePoint.  
  • FY25_Q1-Q2_PO_Log.xlsx – full purchase-order ledger (Jan–Jun 2025)  
  • Active_Supplier_Contracts_June2025.xlsx – contract abstracts + current price lists  
  • Procurement_Pipeline_July-Sept2025.xlsx – pending/planned commitments

1. Recent Purchase Orders (Jan–Jun 2025)  
   • 128 POs issued, total spend ≈ $4.8 M  
   • Top categories: Electronics components (47%), machined parts (28%), packaging (12%)  
   • Major suppliers: A-Tech ($1.3 M), Global Fasteners ($0.9 M), GreenPack ($0.6 M)

2. Current Supplier Contracts & Pricing  
   • A-Tech: 3-year agreement through 31-Dec-2026; 2 % annual price escalation; Q3 price list uploaded  
   • Global Fasteners: 18-month contract; volume-tier discount up to 7 %  
   • GreenPack: rolling 12-month MSA; raw-material surcharge clause updated May-2025

3. Pending / Planned Commitments  
   • PrecisionMold tooling purchase (~ $350 k) – PO will be issued in July  
   • PolyFlex packaging film renewal – target mid-July  
   • Board Sets build-to-stock order (~ $620 k) slated for August

4. Price Change Outlook & Supply-Chain Risks  
   • Copper pricing: +6 % since April; expect further 3-4 % volatility into Q3  
   • Resin supply tightening; packaging materials may incur 5-7 % surcharge  
   • Ocean freight rates stabilizing; East-Asia lead-time remains 6–8 weeks  
   • ERP migrations at A-Tech & PrecisionMold in July could cause short fulfillment delays

Let me know if you’d like a deeper dive or a quick meeting to walk through the numbers. I’ll keep the SharePoint folder updated as new data comes in.

Best regards,
Jane","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item128_execution_log.json","card_path":"data/agent_cards/item128_recipient.json"}

{"to":["mark@dynatechindustries.com"],"subject":"Procurement Data & Supplier Info – Budget Forecast","body":"Hi Mark,

As requested, please find below a concise overview of the latest procurement data covering the last two quarters (FY-2025 Q1–Q2). Detailed documents are available in our shared “Budget Forecast” folder on SharePoint.

• FY25_Q1-Q2_PO_Log.xlsx – full purchase-order ledger (Jan–Jun 2025)
• Active_Supplier_Contracts_June2025.xlsx – contract abstracts + current price lists
• Procurement_Pipeline_July-Sept2025.xlsx – pending/planned commitments

1. Recent Purchase Orders (Jan–Jun 2025)
   • 128 POs issued; total spend ≈ $4.8 M
   • Top categories: electronics components (47 %), machined parts (28 %), packaging (12 %)
   • Major suppliers: A-Tech ($1.3 M), Global Fasteners ($0.9 M), GreenPack ($0.6 M)

2. Current Supplier Contracts & Pricing
   • A-Tech – 3-year agreement through 31-Dec-2026; 2 % annual escalation; Q3 price list uploaded
   • Global Fasteners – 18-month contract; volume-tier discount up to 7 %
   • GreenPack – rolling 12-month MSA; raw-material surcharge clause updated May-2025

3. Pending / Planned Commitments
   • PrecisionMold tooling purchase (~ $350 k) – PO to be issued in July
   • PolyFlex packaging film renewal – target mid-July
   • Board Sets build-to-stock order (~ $620 k) slated for August

4. Price-Change Outlook & Supply-Chain Risks
   • Copper pricing: +6 % since April; expect a further 3-4 % volatility into Q3
   • Resin supply tightening; packaging materials may incur 5-7 % surcharge
   • Ocean freight rates stabilizing; East-Asia lead-time remains 6–8 weeks
   • ERP migrations at A-Tech & PrecisionMold in July could cause short fulfillment delays

Let me know if you’d like a deeper dive or a quick meeting to walk through the numbers. I’ll keep the SharePoint folder updated as new data comes in.

Best regards,
Jane"}
